Return the output


Don‚Äôt forget to return the object you want displayed in the function! Otherwise the output will not render.

The data reacts to the input
dat = load_penguins()

@render.plot
def plot():
    species = input.species() #&lt;&lt;
    sel = dat.loc[dat.species == species] #&lt;&lt;

    return (
        ggplot(aes(x="bill_length_mm"))
        + geom_histogram(dat, fill="#C2C2C4", binwidth=1)
        + geom_histogram(sel, fill="#447099", binwidth=1)
        + theme_minimal()
    )

